                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-text mb-6">Understanding Lower Back Pain: Why Exercise Helps</h2>
                    
                    <p class="text-lg text-text mb-6">
                        Before diving into specific exercises, it's important to understand <em>why</em> movement and exercise are so beneficial for lower back pain. Many people instinctively want to rest when their back hurts, but prolonged inactivity can actually worsen the problem.
                    </p>
                    
                    <div class="card mb-6">
                        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">How Exercise Benefits Your Lower Back:</h3>
                        <ul class="space-y-3 text-text">
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-primary mr-3 mt-1">✓</span>
                                <span><strong>Strengthens Core Muscles:</strong> Your core muscles (including abdominals, back muscles, and pelvic floor) act as a natural corset, providing essential support to your spine.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-primary mr-3 mt-1">✓</span>
                                <span><strong>Increases Flexibility:</strong> Tight muscles, especially in the hamstrings and hip flexors, can contribute to lower back pain by altering your posture and movement patterns.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-primary mr-3 mt-1">✓</span>
                                <span><strong>Improves Blood Flow:</strong> Movement promotes circulation, delivering oxygen and nutrients to damaged tissues while flushing out inflammatory chemicals.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-primary mr-3 mt-1">✓</span>
                                <span><strong>Reduces Muscle Tension:</strong> Gentle stretching and controlled movements help release muscle spasms and reduce protective guarding.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="text-primary mr-3 mt-1">✓</span>
                                <span><strong>Enhances Joint Mobility:</strong> Regular movement maintains the health of spinal joints and prevents stiffness.</span>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>

                    <p class="text-lg text-text mb-6">
                        A 2020 systematic review published in the <em>British Journal of Sports Medicine</em> found that exercise therapy was more effective than usual care for chronic lower back pain, with benefits lasting up to 12 months after treatment.
                    </p>
                </section>

