                                <span>Perform just the stretching exercises (#1, #3, #4) for maintenance and recovery (total time: approximately 10 minutes)</span>
                            </div>
                            <div class="grid grid-cols-[auto_1fr] gap-4 items-start">
                                <span class="text-primary font-bold">Weekend:</span>
                                <span>Rest days or gentle yoga/walking</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <div class="card mb-6">
                        <h4 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text mb-4">Important Guidelines:</h4>
                        <ul class="space-y-2 text-text">
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="mr-2">•</span>
                                <span><strong>Start Slowly:</strong> Begin with fewer repetitions and shorter hold times, gradually increasing as you build strength and confidence.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="mr-2">•</span>
                                <span><strong>Listen to Your Body:</strong> Some mild discomfort is normal, but sharp or shooting pain is a warning sign. Stop immediately if you experience severe pain.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="mr-2">•</span>
                                <span><strong>Consistency is Key:</strong> Regular practice yields better results than intense but sporadic exercise sessions.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="mr-2">•</span>
                                <span><strong>Warm Up First:</strong> Spend 5 minutes warming up with gentle walking or light activity before starting your exercises.</span>
                            </li>
                            <li class="flex items-start">
                                <span class="mr-2">•</span>
                                <span><strong>Maintain Good Form:</strong> Quality of movement is more important than quantity of repetitions.</span>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
