                <section class="mb-12">
                    <h2 class="text-3xl font-heading font-bold text-text mb-6">Moving Forward: Your Journey to a Pain-Free Back</h2>
                    
                    <p class="text-lg text-text mb-6">
                        Lower back pain can be frustrating and debilitating, but with consistent effort and the right approach, most people experience significant improvement. These five exercises provide a solid foundation for building a stronger, more resilient back that can handle the demands of daily life.
                    </p>

                    <p class="text-lg text-text mb-6">
                        Remember that recovery is rarely linear—you may have good days and challenging days. The key is persistence and patience. Most people begin noticing improvements within 2-4 weeks of regular practice, with continued benefits accumulating over months.
                    </p>

                    <p class="text-lg text-text mb-6">
                        Beyond these exercises, consider adopting other back-healthy habits:
                    </p>

                    <ul class="space-y-2 text-lg text-text mb-6">
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="mr-2">•</span>
                            <span>Maintain good posture while sitting and standing</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="mr-2">•</span>
                            <span>Take regular breaks from prolonged sitting</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="mr-2">•</span>
                            <span>Use proper lifting techniques (bend at the knees, not the waist)</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="mr-2">•</span>
                            <span>Maintain a healthy weight to reduce stress on your spine</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="mr-2">•</span>
                            <span>Stay active with regular walking, swimming, or other low-impact activities</span>
                        </li>
                        <li class="flex items-start">
                            <span class="mr-2">•</span>
                            <span>Manage stress through relaxation techniques, as tension often manifests as back pain</span>
                        </li>
                    </ul>

